---
title: "Which Christian Tradition is Closest to LDS?"
navPage: closest
navGroup: comparisons
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
<style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    :root {
      --blue:      #1a4f8a;
      --gold:      #c8972b;
      --green:     #2d7a4f;
      --red:       #8a1a1a;
      --catholic:  #8b1a2e;
      --orthodox:  #5a2d82;
      --protestant:#1a6b3a;
      --bg:        #f5f3ee;
      --card:      #ffffff;
      --text:      #1e1e1e;
      --muted:     #5c5c5c;
      --radius:    10px;
      --shadow:    0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.09);
    }
    body { font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif; background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); line-height: 1.7; }

    .topnav { background: #0d2f57; padding: 0 1.5rem; display: flex; align-items: stretch; flex-wrap: wrap; min-height: 2.8rem; }
    .topnav a.home { color: #fff; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.85rem; padding: 0 0.9rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; transition: background 0.15s; }
    .topnav a.home:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
    .nav-item { color: #cde; text-decoration: none; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0 0.9rem; min-height: 2.8rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.35rem; transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s; }
    .nav-item:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: #fff; }
    .nav-group { position: relative; display: flex; align-items: stretch; }
    .nav-toggle { background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer; color: #cde; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0 0.9rem; min-height: 2.8rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.35rem; transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s; }
    .nav-toggle:hover, .nav-group:hover .nav-toggle, .nav-group:focus-within .nav-toggle { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: #fff; }
    .nav-group.active .nav-toggle { color: #fff; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.14); }
    .nav-caret { font-size: 0.6rem; transition: transform 0.2s; }
    .nav-group:hover .nav-caret, .nav-group:focus-within .nav-caret { transform: rotate(180deg); }
    .nav-dropdown { display: none; position: absolute; top: 100%; left: 0; background: #112a4a; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 0 0 8px 8px; min-width: 210px; box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.35); z-index: 200; }
    .nav-group:hover .nav-dropdown, .nav-group:focus-within .nav-dropdown { display: block; }
    .nav-dropdown a { display: block; color: #cde; text-decoration: none; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.83rem; padding: 0.6rem 1.1rem; transition: background 0.12s, color 0.12s; white-space: nowrap; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); }
    .nav-dropdown a:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .nav-dropdown a:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: #fff; }
    .nav-dropdown a.active { color: #ffd080; font-weight: 700; }

    header { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a4060 0%, #0a2030 100%); color: #fff; text-align: center; padding: 3rem 1.5rem 2.2rem; }
    header .icon { font-size: 2.8rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
    header h1 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.4rem); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    header p { font-size: 1rem; opacity: 0.82; max-width: 650px; margin: 0 auto; }

    main { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem 4rem; }

    .intro-banner { background: var(--card); border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); border-radius: var(--radius); box-shadow: var(--shadow); padding: 1.3rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; font-size: 0.97rem; color: var(--muted); }
    .intro-banner strong { color: var(--text); }

    /* Verdict banner */
    .verdict { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d2f57 0%, #1a4f8a 100%); color: #fff; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 2rem 2rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; box-shadow: var(--shadow); }
    .verdict h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; opacity: 0.75; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
    .verdict-row { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .verdict-item { flex: 1; min-width: 180px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1rem 1.1rem; }
    .verdict-item .rank { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; opacity: 0.7; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
    .verdict-item .tradition { font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700; display: block; margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
    .verdict-item .reason { font-size: 0.85rem; opacity: 0.85; line-height: 1.5; }
    .verdict-item.first { background: rgba(200,151,43,0.25); border: 1px solid rgba(200,151,43,0.4); }
    .verdict-item.second { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
    .verdict-item.third { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); }

    /* Scoring table */
    .score-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .score-section h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; color: var(--blue); margin-bottom: 1rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .score-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: separate; border-spacing: 0; border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden; box-shadow: var(--shadow); font-size: 0.88rem; }
    .score-table thead { background: #0d2f57; color: #fff; }
    .score-table thead th { padding: 0.8rem 1rem; text-align: center; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.03em; }
    .score-table thead th:first-child { text-align: left; width: 30%; }
    .score-table thead th.cath { background: var(--catholic); }
    .score-table thead th.orth { background: var(--orthodox); }
    .score-table thead th.prot { background: var(--protestant); }
    .score-table tbody tr:nth-child(even) td { background: #f0ede8; }
    .score-table tbody tr:nth-child(odd) td { background: #fff; }
    .score-table tbody tr:hover td { background: #e8eef7; }
    .score-table td { padding: 0.7rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #e4dfd8; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; }
    .score-table td:first-child { text-align: left; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--blue); }
    .score-table tfoot td { background: #0d2f57 !important; color: #fff; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; padding: 0.8rem 1rem; }
    .score-table tfoot td:first-child { font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; opacity: 0.8; }

    /* Dot ratings */
    .dots { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 3px; }
    .dot { width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; background: #ddd; }
    .dot.on { background: var(--gold); }
    .dot.on.cath { background: var(--catholic); }
    .dot.on.orth { background: var(--orthodox); }
    .dot.on.prot { background: var(--protestant); }

    /* Tradition analysis cards */
    .analysis-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .analysis-card { background: var(--card); border-radius: var(--radius); box-shadow: var(--shadow); overflow: hidden; }
    .analysis-header { padding: 1.2rem 1.4rem; color: #fff; }
    .analysis-header.cath { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--catholic), #4a0d1a); }
    .analysis-header.orth { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--orthodox), #2e1050); }
    .analysis-header.prot { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--protestant), #0a2d18); }
    .analysis-header h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
    .analysis-header .score-badge { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.78rem; opacity: 0.85; }
    .analysis-body { padding: 1.2rem 1.4rem; }
    .analysis-body h4 { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.09em; color: var(--muted); margin: 0.8rem 0 0.3rem; }
    .analysis-body h4:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
    .analysis-body ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.6; }
    .analysis-body ul li { margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
    .analysis-body ul li.close { color: var(--green); }
    .analysis-body ul li.far { color: var(--red); }
    .analysis-body .summary-line { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--muted); border-top: 1px solid #ece8e0; padding-top: 0.8rem; margin-top: 0.8rem; font-style: italic; }

    /* Dimension breakdown */
    .dimension-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
    .dimension-section h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; color: var(--blue); margin-bottom: 1rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .dim-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr; gap: 1rem; align-items: start; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; background: var(--card); border-radius: var(--radius); box-shadow: var(--shadow); padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem; }
    .dim-label { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--blue); }
    .dim-label .dim-winner { display: block; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.07em; margin-top: 0.2rem; padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; display: inline-block; }
    .dim-winner.cath { background: #fde8ec; color: var(--catholic); }
    .dim-winner.orth { background: #f0e8fa; color: var(--orthodox); }
    .dim-winner.prot { background: #e4f2ea; color: var(--protestant); }
    .dim-winner.tie { background: #fdf3e0; color: #8a6000; }
    .dim-body { font-size: 0.91rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
    .dim-body strong { color: var(--text); }

    /* Note box */
    .note-box { background: #fff8e8; border: 1px solid #e8d090; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.2rem 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; font-size: 0.93rem; color: var(--text); }
    .note-box strong { color: #8a6000; }

    footer { text-align: center; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--muted); padding: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid #ddd8d0; }
    @media (max-width: 600px) { .dim-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .verdict-row { flex-direction: column; } }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<header>
  <span class="icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-ranking-star"></i></span>
  <h1>Which Christian Tradition is Closest to LDS?</h1>
  <p>A doctrine-by-doctrine analysis ranking Catholic, Eastern Orthodox, and Protestant Christianity by how closely each aligns with Latter-day Saint theology.</p>
</header>

<main>

  <div class="intro-banner">
    <strong>Methodology:</strong> Each tradition is scored across 12 key LDS doctrinal categories on a 1–3 scale (1 = far, 2 = partial overlap, 3 = close). No tradition scores highly overall — LDS theology is genuinely distinct — but the comparison reveals where each tradition overlaps most.
  </div>

  <!-- VERDICT -->
  <div class="verdict">
    <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-trophy"></i> &nbsp;Overall Verdict</h2>
    <div class="verdict-row">
      <div class="verdict-item first">
        <span class="rank">&#127941; Closest Overall</span>
        <span class="tradition">Roman Catholic</span>
        <span class="reason">Shares the most structural DNA: hierarchical authority, sacraments as necessary for salvation, apostolic claims, organized clergy, and a living head of the church.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="verdict-item second">
        <span class="rank">&#129352; Second Closest</span>
        <span class="tradition">Eastern Orthodox</span>
        <span class="reason">Shares the most theologically provocative overlap — the theosis/exaltation concept — and a similar emphasis on ongoing sanctification, sacramental mysteries, and the early Church.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="verdict-item third">
        <span class="rank">&#129353; Third Closest</span>
        <span class="tradition">Protestant</span>
        <span class="reason">Shares the most in worship style, missionary emphasis, personal faith, and (in Baptist traditions) baptism by immersion — but the Five Solas create the deepest theological rift.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SCORING TABLE -->
  <div class="score-section">
    <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-table"></i> &nbsp;Doctrine-by-Doctrine Scorecard</h2>
    <p style="font-size:0.88rem; color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:1rem;">Scale: &#11035;&#11035;&#11035; = Close &nbsp;|&nbsp; &#11035;&#11035;&#9711; = Partial &nbsp;|&nbsp; &#11035;&#9711;&#9711; = Far &nbsp;|&nbsp; &#9711;&#9711;&#9711; = Very Different</p>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto;">
      <table class="score-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>LDS Belief / Practice</th>
            <th class="cath"><i class="fa-solid fa-feather"></i> Catholic</th>
            <th class="orth"><i class="fa-solid fa-peace"></i> Orthodox</th>
            <th class="prot"><i class="fa-solid fa-book-open"></i> Protestant</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Living head of the church with prophetic authority</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Sacraments / ordinances necessary for salvation</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot on orth"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Ordained priesthood with exclusive authority</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Human potential to become like God</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot on orth"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Salvation = grace + works / covenant keeping</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Baptism by immersion, for believing adults only</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Organized global church structure (not congregational)</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Scripture beyond the Bible</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Lay (non-celibate, unpaid local) clergy</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot on prot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Strong missionary / evangelism culture</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot on prot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Emphasis on tithing &amp; financial commitment</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot on cath"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on orth"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot on prot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Pre-mortal existence of souls</td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
            <td><div class="dots"><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div><div class="dot"></div></div></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
        <tfoot>
          <tr>
            <td>Total Score (out of 36)</td>
            <td style="color: #ffccaa; font-size: 1.3rem;">21</td>
            <td style="color: #ddaaff; font-size: 1.3rem;">17</td>
            <td style="color: #aaddbb; font-size: 1.3rem;">10</td>
          </tr>
        </tfoot>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- DIMENSION ANALYSIS -->
  <div class="dimension-section">
    <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-chart-bar"></i> &nbsp;Breakdown by Dimension</h2>

    <div class="dim-row">
      <div class="dim-label">Church Structure &amp; Authority<span class="dim-winner cath"><i class="fa-solid fa-feather"></i> Catholic wins</span></div>
      <div class="dim-body">LDS and Catholicism are structurally the most alike of any two religions on earth. Both have a global hierarchical organization, a single living head with universal authority, a quorum of apostles/cardinals, bishops overseeing geographic areas, and the claim of exclusive divine authority. <strong>Orthodox</strong> is somewhat similar (synodal bishops) but no single head. <strong>Protestantism</strong> is decentralized — often the opposite of LDS structure.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="dim-row">
      <div class="dim-label">Human Potential &amp; Deification<span class="dim-winner orth"><i class="fa-solid fa-peace"></i> Orthodox wins</span></div>
      <div class="dim-body">Eastern Orthodoxy's doctrine of <em>theosis</em> — that humans can become partakers of the divine nature — is the closest parallel to LDS exaltation in all of Christianity. Both cite 2 Peter 1:4 and early Church Fathers like Irenaeus ("God became man that man might become God"). The key difference: Orthodox theosis is participation in God's energies while remaining creatures; LDS exaltation means literally becoming gods. <strong>Catholicism</strong> teaches the beatific vision but not deification. <strong>Protestantism</strong> generally rejects any form of deification.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="dim-row">
      <div class="dim-label">Salvation Theology<span class="dim-winner cath"><i class="fa-solid fa-feather"></i> Catholic wins</span></div>
      <div class="dim-body">Both LDS and Catholicism reject <em>sola fide</em> (faith alone). Both teach that salvation requires grace <em>and</em> human cooperation — through sacraments/ordinances, ongoing repentance, and faithful living. <strong>Orthodox</strong> is similar (salvation as theosis through the mysteries) but frames it differently. <strong>Protestantism's</strong> core doctrine of faith alone is the sharpest contrast to LDS soteriology.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="dim-row">
      <div class="dim-label">Baptism<span class="dim-winner prot"><i class="fa-solid fa-book-open"></i> Protestant (Baptist) wins</span></div>
      <div class="dim-body">On the specific practice of baptism, <strong>Baptist and Evangelical Protestantism</strong> is closest to LDS — both require a personal profession of faith, baptism of believers only (not infants), and full immersion. Catholic and Orthodox infant baptism by sprinkling/pouring is furthest from LDS practice. However, LDS baptism also includes proxy work for the dead — unique to LDS.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="dim-row">
      <div class="dim-label">Scripture &amp; Revelation<span class="dim-winner tie">All Three Equally Far</span></div>
      <div class="dim-body">None of the three traditions accepts the Book of Mormon, Doctrine &amp; Covenants, or Pearl of Great Price as scripture. None accepts a living prophet who can add new binding revelation. All three hold their own closed canon as complete. This is the single most unique and non-negotiable LDS distinction — and every mainstream tradition is equally far from it.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="dim-row">
      <div class="dim-label">Worship Style &amp; Culture<span class="dim-winner prot"><i class="fa-solid fa-book-open"></i> Protestant wins</span></div>
      <div class="dim-body">LDS sacrament meetings are simple, lay-led, congregational, and centered on talks and hymns — resembling Evangelical Protestant services far more than a Catholic Mass or Orthodox Divine Liturgy. There are no liturgical robes, incense, icons, or chanting. The informality and emphasis on personal testimony feel most Protestant in character.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="dim-row">
      <div class="dim-label">Missions &amp; Evangelism<span class="dim-winner prot"><i class="fa-solid fa-book-open"></i> Protestant wins</span></div>
      <div class="dim-body">LDS missionary culture — two-year full-time missions, door-to-door outreach, personal testimony sharing — parallels Evangelical and Pentecostal Protestant traditions far more than Catholic or Orthodox practice. Orthodoxy has historically been less missionary-focused; Catholicism's missions are primarily administered through religious orders rather than lay members.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="dim-row">
      <div class="dim-label">Nature of God (Trinity)<span class="dim-winner tie">All Three Equally Far</span></div>
      <div class="dim-body">All three mainstream traditions affirm the Nicene Trinity — one God in three co-equal persons of the same substance. LDS explicitly rejects this formulation, teaching three separate beings. This is the primary reason mainstream Christianity does not recognize LDS as Trinitarian Christian. All three are equally committed to the Nicene Creed on this point.</div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- TRADITION ANALYSIS CARDS -->
  <div class="score-section">
    <h2><i class="fa-solid fa-magnifying-glass"></i> &nbsp;Tradition-by-Tradition Analysis</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="analysis-grid">

